as only 2 blocks from the 96th Street Subway Terminal which was really great too...Time Square was only about 10 minutes away via the subway. There was a couple of diners nearby as well as a McDonalds and Dunkin Donuts which was great for breakfast. There was also two 24 hour grocerie stores open where you could pick up a few things. The neighborhood itself was very safe.I'd say if you're on a budget and are just looking for a place to sleep then the Grant Hotel is perfect. It doesn't really make sense to spend hundreds of dollars on a room because it's New York and you are obviously going to be out walking around for most of the day looking at all of the tourist sites. The next time I go back to New York I'll definitely stay here again.	
